itemListElement.name: Seattle, Mount Rainier National Park 2-Day Tour from Seattle

name: Seattle, Mount Rainier National Park 2-Day Tour from Seattle
description:
Welcome to Washington state’s largest city, Seattle! 
Trace back to the birthplace of Starbucks and enjoy its most original taste.
Visit iconic sites and attractions in Seattle such as Sky View Observatory at Columbia Center and the Space Needle!
Explore the unique landscape at Mount Rainier and all that it has to offer.
Enjoy the natural beauty of Mt. Rainier with its spectacular waterfalls (Christine, Narada, Myrtle), vast lakes and lush green forests.

Room Details
All hotel rooms are based on two Full / Double beds or one King/Queen bed depends on what hotel availiable on the day. The maximum occupancy per room is four travelers.

One Room Selection 
If you are a party of more than four guests or desire to have separate rooms, please provide a separate booking.

Avoid traveling in a different bus?
If you have more than one booking, please provide all confirmation numbers once your bookings are complete.

itemListElement.name: Hop On Hop Off Must See Seattle Tour

name: Hop On Hop Off Must See Seattle Tour
description:
From the Open Top Double-decker buses you get the best view of Seattle and its beautiful surroundings with mountains and Puget sound.
The City Sightseeing Seattle Must See Seattle Tour is the only Hop on Hop off tour in Seattle. With 16 stops throughout the city and busses running every 20-30 minutes, this tour is the perfect way to explore the Emerald City at your own pace.
The ticket is valid for 24 hours from time of boarding the first bus and allows you unlimited rides from 10:00am to 5:00pm.
The tour passes most of Seattle's many points of interest like Space Needle. Seattle Center. The Monorail. MoPoP. Pacific Science Center. Sky View Observatory. International district with Japantown and Chinatown. Edgewater Hotel. Pier 66 Norwegian Cruise Line. Seattle Aquarium. Pier 55 Miners Landing. Seattle Waterfront. Historic Pioneer Square. UPS Waterfall Garden Park. Historic Chinatown Gate. Capitol Hill. Starbucks Reserve. Fallen firefighter memorial. Pike Place Market and much more...

review.name: Excellent tour bus
review.reviewBody:
Great experience today on the tour bus the driver was brilliant added lots of information to the informative recording along the way 
The driver stopped along the way and added lots of fun facts information & stories was really good 
Well worth the money sat upstairs it was a lovely sunny day had to laugh as some of the trees brushed your head !! as quite low 
Absolutely recommend

review.name: Hop on hop off Seattle shambolic
review.reviewBody: Have used hop on hop off bus all over the world. Always good but Seattle s is a farce. On my he 2 days we paid for we rode it 3 times. First day we waited 50 minutes for a bus when brochure states 20 to 30 min. The driver said it was due to driver shortage. 2nd day first bus was supposed to start at 10. It didn’t turn up until 11. Yep it was because of a driver shortage. The bus was full after the first stop. We stayed on for 7 stops and people who had waited for over an hour were turned away at each stop. Shambolic and not fit for purpose would be doing this organisation a favour. Don’t waste $116 as we did. Get an orca card. Cheaper and more reliable

review.name: Thank you City Sightseeing Seattle
review.reviewBody: My family came into seattle for the weekend before a cruise was not tue best weather wise but your staff and drivers made it awesome Thank you for the best service we will be back again

review.name: Worst Hop On Hop Off Ever
review.reviewBody: The stops were difficult to find. No clearly visible signs. Our first driver didn’t stop at the stop where we wanted to get off. He told us we should have told him where we wanted to get off. The recording on the bus was behind on the stops. As we were leaving stops, the announcer would provide the stop number. Map given didn’t have all street names and was hard to follow. We have done Hop On Ho Off tours all over the world and this was our first real disappointment.

review.name: efficient but a little dull
review.reviewBody: I am sort of a fan of hop on hop off tours, mostly for the informational content, and occasional bad joke.  This seattle one sort of phones it in.  Its a recorded, english only tour with a lot of this is that building stuff but not a lot of background and trivia and almost no humor.  Too bad the subject is interesting.  Hope they jazz up this tour

review.name: Couldn’t use
review.reviewBody: I purchased this ticket for Saturday Sept 21st and was unable to even use it. I went to get on a bus and the driver said they ended at 4:00 , it was like 4:10. ( This was after spending 3 hours at the needle ) They also said the evening rides were cancelled. So I’m out 39.00 for this ticket and 25.00 in parking. He said I could use it tomorrow but when your visiting from out of state for a Cruise you can’t just change that. Very disappointed

review.name: Take this tour with the chance that you may not get to complete the full route
review.reviewBody:
I understand that the buses are very dependent on traffic conditions and passengers may end up waiting more than half an hour before the buses arrive. The company should develop an app to track buses real time (like Big Bus) or view current buses plying the routes on a website (like Free Waterfront Shuttle). 

i had a bad experience today (20th Sept) where i waited at the Chinatown stop for more than an hour (4pm to 5.20pm) and still had no bus come by. our intention was to hop on within the 4pm hour to complete the route and be back to Space Needle station before the service ends at 6pm. there was no way for me to check if there was any route closure or traffic jams. 
I eventually had to take the Free Waterfront Shuttle back to Space Needle and forfeit the rest of the tour. 

Narrated tour was quite well thought of and included nice tidbit of information. Narration could be heard over normal traffic sounds as well. 

The condition of the bus left much to improve on; dead leaves and hardened up rubbish left behind for months coat the floor of the top deck. 

I should think their other tours (guided) might be a better choice as the buses looked decent and had a live guide to bring you around.

review.name: Good way to get around Seattle and see the sights as well
review.reviewBody:
Our group of four took this tour to see more of the city. The price was ok, but we really didn't see that many places of real interest. The fact that you can get on and off at various points around the city made this tour worth while. Sadly, the homeless and derelicts abound in Seattle and they almost seem to be on every corner. Unfortunately their use of restrooms is limited so the streets become their place to go. We saw a number of people exposing themselves and greatly detracted from the actual tour. Perhaps the City of Seattle turns a blind eye to this behavior, but it is a problem that needs serious attention.

A word of caution: If you park mind your time. This tour can take quite some time and even more so if you decide to get off the bus. The parking downtown is metered and they watch the time you are parked there very closely. A delay on this tour can cost you big time if you go over your cars parking time!

review.name: Best way to see the city and attractions
review.reviewBody:
Enjoyed the tour hoped on and off the bus at different attractions 
Knowledgeable staff and safe happy drivers very informative and fun 
Great views of the city and water front

review.name: Worst hop-on-hop-off ever
review.reviewBody: We have done several hop-on-hop-off tours around the US and Europe. All were great. So we wanted to do this in Seattle as well. But: first of all - almost no information. You cannot find the stops. No persons around at most of them. Hardly visible signs. So we went to Space Needle and... finally ... found it. Went on the bus around 9.55am. Expected start 10h. AND... had to wait some 30 minutes, without any explanation! Then we started - no audio system working. Bus driver didn't stop at all the places. People wanted to get off at Waterfront, but he didn't stop. We did not dare to get off the bus because you can absolutely not rely on them! We cannot recommend this company.

itemListElement.name: Full Day Private Cascades Hiking & Snoqualmie Falls Tour

name: Full Day Private Cascades Hiking & Snoqualmie Falls Tour
description:
Get ready for a full-day hiking and waterfalls adventure into the Cascade Mountains! And get ready for more than just a hiking trip: with a local tour guide, you’ll learn about the area’s natural and cultural history, get to know native plants and wildlife, and be guided to some of the best trails in Washington!

We don’t have to drive far to experience the best hikes near Seattle – it’s just knowing where they are! Your knowledgeable tour guide will know which trails are right for your group and how much we can tackle in one day.

Enjoy an easy to moderate hike to photogenic waterfalls as your tour guide narrates the natural history and ecology of the Pacific Northwest. While waterfall hikes in Washington are popular, we can take on more challenging Washington hikes to be rewarded with fantastic summit views.

As a reward, we’ll stop at the majestic Snoqualmie Falls, offering breathtaking views, and end with an optional stop at a brewery, winery, or cidery before returning to Seattle!

name: Escape Room Activity in Seattle
description: Our escape room experience is a thrilling journey, crafted with meticulous attention to detail and infused with immersive narratives that transport players to extraordinary worlds. Each room is a symphony of challenges, combining intricate puzzles, clever riddles, and hidden clues that demand teamwork, logic, and creativity to unravel. What sets us apart is our dedication to innovation, constantly pushing the boundaries of traditional escape rooms with cutting-edge technology and dynamic storytelling. From the moment you step inside, you're not just a player—you're part of an unforgettable adventure, where every decision matters and every triumph feels earned.

review.name: Family Fun
review.reviewBody: Afternoon well spent with family at 4Dreams escape room. We couldn’t escape so looks like we are going to try our luck again. Highly recommend if you are looking for a fun activity with your family and friends.

review.name: Best of bestest
review.reviewBody: We did this room during our short visit to Seattle and loved the experience! The staff was super friendly and very helpful. The rooms were well-designed with cool details that made us feel like we were really part of the story. The puzzles were tough but doable, and we had a great time working together to solve them. They are arcade style, so definitely not your traditional escape room expectation, which was very refreshing! We managed to complete 3 rooms out of 4, which I consider being success! Highly recommend!

review.name: Must try
review.reviewBody:
Amazing experience!!! We will definitely come back. It was absolutely amazing.
Alex is the best. I suggest everyone to try this place

itemListElement.name: West Seattle Sunset Sea Kayak Tour

name: West Seattle Sunset Sea Kayak Tour
description:
Experience the Beautiful West Seattle Sunset by Sea Kayak. This is the most iconic view - the sunsetting behind the Olympic mountains with the Seattle city skyline behind you. 

After a brief boat fitting and paddling instruction, we first head out on the water to search for wildlife at the mouth of the Duwamish river.

Next, we’re off to Duwamish Head for views of the islands as the sun melts into the Olympic Mountains and creates a light show off the downtown Seattle skyline. Enjoy the sunset from the best vantage point in town!

name: Alki Lighthouse Sea Kayak Tour
description:
This tour is offered no where else in Seattle. This is an offshore Sea Kayak Tour to Alki Lighthouse in West Seattle
This is an exciting sea kayak tour from the Seacrest Boathouse (Marination) to the Alki Lighthouse and back. Get offshore with us and explore Elliott Bay on an adventure that has new surprises every day.

We meet at 10 a.m. and, after a brief kayak fitting and tutorial, get in the boats and head on around Duwamish Head toward Alki beach.

Incredible views of the city, the Cascade Mountains, and the Olympic Mountains provide the backdrop for an urban wildlife exploration and journey along a peninsula rich in history.

itemListElement.name: Admiral's Legacy Family-Friendly Outdoor Scavenger Hunt

name: Admiral's Legacy Family-Friendly Outdoor Scavenger Hunt
description:
Immerse yourself in an exhilarating urban adventure: Experience the thrill of exploring West Seattle’s vibrant streets, iconic landmarks, and hidden gems as you solve puzzles and unravel clues.

Flexible group sizes: Whether you’re flying solo, with a partner, or in a large group of up to 100, our scavenger hunts cater to all, fostering teamwork and friendly competition.

Family-friendly fun: Create lasting memories as you bond with loved ones while discovering Seattle’s rich history and culture together. Our scavenger hunts offer an exciting and educational experience suitable for all ages.
